\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_eos$fit_bspp_per95[which(bspp_df2_ts_eos$spp_name %in% "Tilia americana")]}]))
, except \Ball for which its growth decreased with later end of season ($\beta = $
\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_eos$fit_bspp[which(bspp_df2_ts_eos$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]}, $UI_{90}$[\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_eos$fit_bspp_per5[which(bspp_df2_ts_eos$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]},
\Sexpr{bspp_df2_ts_eos$fit_bspp_per95[which(bspp_df2_ts_eos$spp_name %in% "Betula alleghaniensis")]}]) (Figure \ref{fig:wcmuplotbsppTS} d) and h)). The estimates were unchanged when using the full or restricted datasets ($n =$\Sexpr{nrow(empfulleosts)} vs $n=$\Sexpr{nrow(empts)} Figure \ref{fig:tsSOSEOScomparison} (b)).

% Effect size across species
\item 

\end{enumerate}
